# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Modernized recreation of the MSU/CAVS tutorials by Mark A. Tschopp
# Tutorial 1: Crystalline metals and the EAM potential -- shifted cell
# Same as minimize.lmp, but the lattice origin is shifted off the box faces.

# 1) Initialization
units metal
dimension 3
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic

# 2) System definition
# Shift the lattice origin by a quarter spacing so that no atoms sit exactly
# on the box faces (fcc has lattice planes every half spacing, so a 0.5 region
# shift would still land on the face-centered plane).
lattice fcc 4.05 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 4 0 4 0 4
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 256 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds

# 3) Settings
pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * Al_zhou.eam.alloy Al
Reading eam/alloy potential file Al_zhou.eam.alloy with DATE: 2007-10-12

compute eng all pe/atom
compute eatoms all reduce sum c_eng

# 4) Monitoring
thermo 10
thermo_style custom step pe c_eatoms press lx pxx pyy pzz

# 5) Run
fix relax all box/relax iso 0.0 vmax 0.001
min_style cg
minimize 1.0e-12 1.0e-12 10000 100000
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
  max neighbors/atom: 2000, page size: 100000
  master list distance cutoff = 12.1025
  ghost atom cutoff = 12.1025
  binsize = 6.05125, bins = 3 3 3
  1 neighbor lists, perpetual/occasional/extra = 1 0 0
  (1) pair eam/alloy, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
